caption: Best sushi in the area. Highly recommend the omakase, no need for the special ones, the sushi omakase has amazing variety and the fish is very fresh.

Have eaten here several times. Great food. But recently ordered via delivery. They did not send (2) rolls. Spoke to them and they said they would send an order out. 2 hrs later nobody sent anything. Call back and then took no responsibility. They communicated that food was being delivered (took our address) only to later say they were not going to do anything about it.
been coming here since 2014, amazing food!

This is and will always will be my favorite sushi spot in NYC. Every other spot always gets compared to Katsuei, and always looses. Omakase is of course my favorite thing to get. It constantly changes depending on the season but it’s always amazing! My husband tried sushi for the first time in his life here, and it will always be our special place.

First-rate vibes and super friendly service. The food was crisp and yummy. Will surely recommend this restaurant to friends and family. Reasonable rates and generous meals. Keep it up.

We've been to this restaurant a handful of times now and have never been disappointed.  Great service, great atmosphere, lots of seating by windows and outdoors (good during COVID).  The menu is inventive and well-executed.  Definitely a go-to for me and my boyfriend as it's pretty easy to get a table (because the restaurant is huge!).

Cant go wrong with $50 Omakase.... actually, you can. Very, very wrong. So I'm not sure how they pull it off, but the fish is fresh and they have an amazing selection. If you speak conversational Japanese and sit at the counter, you'll find some very special and rare Sashimi and Sushi pieces sitting on your tray. Good selection of Sake as well. I highly recommend the Sashimi Omakase vs the Sushi/Sashimi.
Some of the best fish I've ever had. Fantastic Omakase and sushi! Great staff! Covid precautions, lovely outdoor seating. Highly recommend!
Great food and amazing service, I would go here anytime with friends!
It's not super cheap, but it's affordable for the quality of fish. The service is very kind and authentic. I'd recommend sitting at the sushi bar for the omakase

Tried Omakase sushi set. You get 9 pieces of sushi and a hand roll. The fish was fresh, but to my taste the garnishes had a very strong taste and overpowered the taste of fish. There was a tad too much vinegar in the rice. The handroll was pretty good. Quick service.
The plum peppers some fancy fish sushi was amazing

If you get takeout from this great Sushi Restaurant in South Brooklyn, you get what you pay for. The fish quality is so consistent,its always good takeout even though dining in was always so enjoyable.   They have outdoor seating. Everything they serve is great.

Ordered two omakase sushi, chicken katsu (not pictured), and a 24 oz wakatake onikoroshi junmai sake. The food was amazing - fresh, tasty. Outdoor seating with 6 feet distancing. Hand sanitizer and bath room offered prior to seating. All plates and utensils are disposal.

I really enjoyed the food.  The ambience was a bit crowded and loud, but the food makes it worth it.
Best sushi in Brooklyn by a long mile and you need to spend double in Manhattan for much better than this.  Just shutup and go eat here.
8/10 omakase. Quality fish
Fresh fish, fresh ginger, great service

Sushi was amazing - but I ordered take out (enough for half of a meal) and was going to combine that with leftovers from lunch - I ordered, thinking I’m already paying $25 for almost nothing potion-wise, but hey, the quality is apparently unbeatable - to the price jumping to $40 when I got there - The portion was so small - I’ve never paid that much for sushi in my entire life....it didn’t help that the staff is seemingly over the top rude - I walked in nicely asking for my take out and the woman responded by rolling her eyes, saying “yeah, yeah” and heaving it onto the counter....I’ve read reviews like this before, so I guess I wouldn’t advise against eating here, but I would say to NEVER GET TAKE OUT HERE, and be prepared to deal with some attitude and overpriced sushi.
Its a bit overpriced .... but good food not going to lie. Service was good until the server gave my bill while I’m still chewing my last bite...I was a little shocked there.
I come here for my Birthday every year and I love it. The omakase is amazing and the wait staff is nice and attentive.

The interior is clean and relaxing. Sushi Katsuei is packed. Luckily we made a reservation ahead of time and were sat in the other room.  We all ordered the sushi and sashimi omakase which took a while to be served. We were pretty hungry by the time the sashimi arrived. I enjoyed the oyster. The toro was not as melt-in-your-mouth as I was expecting. The rest of the omakase was, however, well-paced. The Santa Barbara uni was so sweet! I wish I could have gotten more. The rest of the sushi pieces did not really stand out to me.  4 stars for the service and the availability of omakase in Brooklyn is great. 3 stars for the actual food because nothing really stood out to me and for the price. Sushi Katsuei's omakase is pricier than most places in Manhattan.

Far and away the best sushi in the neighborhood.  Good variety of fish, all very fresh, at a price point that is far less than what you would pay in Manhattan for similar quality.  Definitely recommend going with the omakase.  Have gotten takeout and eaten there quite often since initial review and it is still amazing. Of course it is a lot more delicious to eat there but taking out is still excellent.

One of the best places in park slope. Highest quality fish being served here. It's all about the chefs menu ..sit back and let the chef do his job. The flavors and freshness are just that incredible. So simple but done so right .
So fresh wow!!

Plates looked worn out. We ordered agedashi tofu but it was disappointing. Omakase - they are tasty but I would not expect all fish is pre-cut and placed on their working table. It makes them less fresh and not cold enough either. I know the price is relatively lower than other omakase restaurants, but I still had high hopes on it because of its good reviews. However, we didn’t feel very content after the course. Don’t think we would go back again.

Great omakase in Brooklyn. About 70 dollars for the sushi and sashimi pairing great deal!

Made advance reservations and went there for the sushi/sushimi omakase. Service was very prompt and attentive. Prices were in line with other higher grade sushi restaurants in NYC. Obviously, the grade of fish drives the pricing to a large degree and the quality was superb. Note the fat in the otoro and the color of the Uni. The real magic is in the seasoning and balance and their sushi chefs have great skills here. It’s almost perfect - to the point they don’t supply you with soy sauce or wasabi and warn you not to use soy sauce with most pieces.  In a nutshell: this is a highly recommended place in Brooklyn that you should make the effort to visit.
I would say for sure this is one of the best places I've been in America for sushi. I would mark this 4 star in Japan to be honest but they are very good!

Exquisite.

This was our first Omakase and our first melt-in-mouth sushi. The quality of the cuts used and the generous portion at the price level makes this Omakase a steal for mid range sushi.  For $52 we got 8 pieces of sushi and a handroll. On the side we ordered octopus tempura, california maki roll and a shrimp tempura roll. All of the food was above excellent but the Omakase sushi was divine.  The only meh pieces were the white fish and the uni (California origins unfortunately on that night as they didn't have the Japanese variety). The chef was very clear with the origin of each piece (more than half were Japanese) and the dressing used.  The pieces dressing for some pieces was a bit overwhelming especially the ones with Wasabi but my wife managed to eat her pieces despite the fact she hates spicy food and wasabi in general.  The service and the rythm were on point, explanatory enough without being overwhelming or too fast. Most importantly no pushing to buy expensive drinks or Sake, but willing to recommend or explain any option on the menu.  The only downside is that it is a relatively small Omakase menu so the chef was preparing different pieces to others that looked exceptional that we wished we had too. In the future it would be great to have an option for 12 or 15 pieces Omakase at a higher price point to let the customers try all of the different cuts available.

I know the quality can't be, and shouldn't be compared, and this is also a cheaper omakase but still.... The food was delicious! Everything was very fresh and beautifully presented. Service was excellent.

Really good Japanese sushi. Recommend not to think over your choices. Say Omakase (chef choice). It's premium selection of fish. No worry. It's worth to be surprised.

Hands down the absolute best sushi I've eaten in my life. Extremely fresh and tasty fish served with passion and precision. Excellent staff, excellent restaurant, enchanting food. Thanks for a memorable birthday evening!

This was our first omakase experience. It was so good, so fresh and so freaking yummy. They have different omakase options which is good because it tailors to whether you're more sushi/sashimi lover. Can't wait to come back.

The best sushi for it's price in the city, as far as I'm concerned, and in my opinion, there's no other reason to go there than to sit at the bar and order omakase. ***FOOD POISONING*** My husband and I went out for dinner to Sushi Katsuei on Saturday night. We had a great time whilst we were there. Unfortunately some time after I got home, I realised I had food poisoning. I was sick 9 times through the night. I have a tough stomach and have never been in a condition like this before. The reason I am certain this was due to the Sushi Katsuei meal is that I had nothing to eat after or prior to that meal, the last food I consumed was lunch. We spend $325 on the meal. I called the restaurant 3 times yesterday unable to speak to the manager. The last time I called asking for the manager, I spoke to a woman who works there. She said, that I would need to provide a Dr’s note to prove that I was specifically sick by something at their restaurant. This would not be possible since I had stopped physically being sick. She also was very quick to advise me that my stomach was probably not that strong and that perhaps I couldn’t handle the food. I have been eating sushi my entire adult life and never had this happen to me. It’s not unknown that you could get sick from one bad oyster which we had and from one cut of fish but not another. She also said it might have been something I ate from my fridge that made me sick. My initial approach to this was that these things happen and I know that this isn’t a restaurant that would intentionally serve bad food. I was looking to be comp’d, even partially yes especially because of how much we spent. I never in a million years expected the insensitivity and rude response I got from this restaurant. Like I wasn’t feeling bad enough the then go on and receive countless criticisms in addition to being cut off in the middle of conversation. Needless to say, I will never go back to Sushi Katsuei. It was the worst dining experience I’d ever had.

Sushi is very fresh and omakase incorporates perfect balance of flavors. Wide selection of fish options. Service is swift and attentive and prices are reasonable for the quality of the fish. Definitely recommend.
fantastic omakase at an affordable price. highly recommend!
Great fish, great service! Omakase at the bar is highly recommended. I just left a bit hungry, but hey, quality over quantity.

This is one of the best Sushi places I've been to. It's Yasuda-level, but without all the pose.  The place isn't fancy, but it's nice and cozy, and the service is really good.  The sushi is really similar to the one you would find in Japan, significantly better than 99% of places in NYC (with the exception of Yasuda, which is also good, but has terrible and awkward service). We got a seat at the bar and ordered the open ended omakase. Every dish served was amazing and had its own mix of flavors and textures. Unlike traditional Japanese omakase this place is made to serve a large amount of people so while the chef does tell you what fish it is and what goes on or into it they don't go into detail explain in depth or help new people learn to eat real sushi.  That being said because they serve a large number of people it helps keep the price down and is the cheapest omakase I've been to in the US. The service was great and food was amazing I highly suggest this place and will be returning many times.
Great sushi priced fantastically. Hands-down the best omakase deal in NYC.
Food was amazing! I will definitely come back.
Best sushi ever
Fun to sit at the bar and watch the chefs
Excellent 🍣
Absolutely amazing!! Love this place. Been to dozens of sushi joints in NYC and this is tops. No frills, almost dive-ish, decent service, and excellent sushi and sake selection!!
Great tasting menu! I miss places like this living in Westchester. Enjoy it you spoiled brooklynites!

Com here every week. Service and food is the best. Will be coming back again and again
This is by far the best sushi place in brooklyn! It is so good I 10/10 would recommend to any sushi lover. Would eat here everyday if I could.

We zipped in for a quick meal the other night. They were very gracious to accommodate us since we didn't have a reservation. The food was very good.  We shared the snow peas salad with bonito flakes. It was very light and flavorful. I has the sashimi deluxe and my boyfriend has the sushi deluxe. The quality of the fish was excellent. The waiter was very thorough about explaining what each fish was. Many of the people around us were taking advantage of their omakase menu which is said to be the best in Brooklyn.  We are looking forward to having a longer meal there in the future, but it was a very good Japanese restaurant which is very appreciated since we have a lot of mediocre ones.

Good sushi, but rude service - we understood the goal was authenticity, but, especially with the pricey food, the waitress didn't need to scoff at my friends for asking for hot sauce and for more soy sauce.
Had the omakase here. Excellent sushi – however, I'm not convinced that it's worth the price. Also, the interior was a bit too starkly lit and loud with conversations for my taste.

Not worth the money! On Tuesday, August 22 2017 my wife and I went based on what we thought were good reviews. We each took the $60 Omakase. Omakase always means at least a few little plates before the sushi. Nope. Not even a soup. Then the sushi, which appeared quite fresh, well cut and presented, had an over abundance of wasabi to the point where you could in no way taste the fish. When we made the very kind server aware of this, nothing changed. Another plate, made her aware, nothing changed. We did not pay $60 a plate to eat wasabi and go home hungry. Lastly, I asked why my cold sake was so expensive when I pointed on the menu and ordered the carafe. Turns out there are two sizes of carafe, and even though I showed our very nice server what I wanted, she brought me the one that was twice the price ($45!). The restaurant made no attempt to correct their mistake. My wife and I, we do not make a scene. We leave and advise our entire circle of fellow Village residents never to visit this place. Predict they close by spring with no attitude and chef changes. STAY AWAY!
Love this place.   Great food and great service.   If you are looking for an authentic japanese sushi place in brooklyn,  this one is a must go!
